text.__SUMMARY__: Odostomella metata is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.
text.Distribution: This marine species is endemic to New Zealand.
text.References: Schander, C.; Hori, S.; Lundberg, J. (1999). Anatomy and phylogeny of Odostomella and Herviera (Mollusca, Heterogastropoda, Pyramidellidae), with a description of a new species of Odostomella. Ophelia. 51(1), 39-76 page(s): 57
